channel.title: i STILL CANT POST IT AGAIN...
channel.description: some1 gave me advice to change my ip to a no-ip or else i cant post more servers. and no1 could see my server posted so i did that and posted my no-ip. now my no-ip isnt listed and no1's getting on anymore. i make a diffrent no-ip and try to post it but it says i cant post more then 1. AGAIN i see thousands of "lost isles"(those peeps should be banned, or muted or something) anyway im like wtf they post thosands of times but i cant post more then 2? some1 plz tell me what rong?

item.title: i STILL CANT POST IT AGAIN...
item.dc:creator: @Evanz Evanz
item.description:
@Evanz wrote:

If they have a dynamic ip then they just restart their router, giving them a new ip.
This means the server status reads that the ip is not yet registerd to the page.
Therefore it adds it,

~Evanz~
